track_notes: Good sized parking area.  Bit scrubby walking, partly overgrown, but very direct.

From the South Stack RSPB reserve car park (RSPB shop with cafe and toilets) take the public right of way (posted Private Land), rising to the plateau south west of Holyhead Mountain. The PROW joins with the Angelsey Coastal Path - follow to north east.

A path marked Summit ends up back on the Coastal Path, so not very helpful! Shortly after, turn to the right up steep rock steps. Soon you will be by the summit trig point.

About 25 minutes each way.
track_title: From South Stack RSPB car park

track_notes: Having taken shortcuts up, we thought we would take official routes back.
track_title: Official paths back to the car park
